{
  "texts": [
    "The state is augmented with the applied torque T and steering angle δ to model the actuator dynamics, and with θ, the progress of the car along the track, resulting in the state vector µ x k = (x, y, ψ, v x, v y, ω, T, δ, θ) ∈ R 9.",
    "These additional states follow simple integrator dynamics, whose corresponding velocities are the control inputs u k. = ( Ṫ, δ, θ) ∈ R 3.",
    "The discrete-time nominal model f in Eq.",
    "( 1) is defined by numerical integration using a fourth-order Runge-Kutta method with three stages inside the sampling interval of ∆T.",
    "= 0.033 [s]."
  ]
}